 special event it is a social event it may be surprising to learn that  of millennials say technology factors into their choice of quickservice restaurants twentyeight percent say that technology factors into their choice of tableservice restaurants according to a  nra restaurant industry forecast according to the generational consumer trend report  of generation z consumers already eat out once a week they are digitally connected and they expect to be able to connect with everyone else in their world anytime they choose restaurants connect with these two groups by extending the dining experience outside the walls of their store here are a few ways they are using technology to engage with the younger generations selfserve ordering using a kiosk and digital table ordering fulfills young diners’ need for instant access and control over transactions innovative selfserve options save time help restaurants reduce the numbers of errors and combat rising labor costs going mobile diners want to be able to view menus online on a mobilefriendly website in fact  of guests use mobile devices to look up restaurant menus on a monthly basis going mobile allows restaurants to link ordering payments and loyalty programs creating a frictionless experience for guests payment options mobile payment options and tableside payment stations are gaining acceptance you can pay when you’re ready to leave which lead to quicker table turns and increased satisfaction revenue and tips according to the nra forecast  of consumers would pay with an app if it were available creating raving fans with loyalty programs more and more restaurants use mobile engagement to show they care for their reward program members emails and phone numbers provide a direct link to guests but guests will only read messages that are interesting and relevant the volume of data gathered when guests order online allows restaurants to send more personalized messages for example if ted enjoys a free strawberry milkshake with his meal on fridays a restaurant can send him an offer for a free milkshake with his meal once a month brand marketers can create invitations for a lunch regular to come back for a happy hour or dinner special customized messages endear guests and create raving fans engaging in social media it is vital that restaurants engage on social media onefourth of restaurant guests and  of millennials take photos of their meal to share recent data shows that  of guests shared positive reviews on social media vs  who shared negative feedback even if children are too young to drive to restaurants they are great influencers since a majority of their information comes from social media it is imperative to be a part of their online conversations according to the  nra restaurant industry forecast  of parents of gen zers choose restaurants based on their children’s suggestions keeping them connected restaurants are finding that offering free wifi plays a significant role in the restaurant choice of both millennials and generation z even though these guests are eating lunch with their friends they’ll still be communicating to their friends on their mobile devices restaurants who build strong relationships with millennials and generation z will create customers for life technology can help restaurants connect with younger guests and give them what they want to find out whats keeping restaurants from embracing mobile guest engagement visit our hospitality blog search blogs filter by industry all ncr blogs everyday made easier retail hospitality financial telecom  technology travel company nora chisnell ambassador program manager other articles by this author blog archivesall related articles mobile guest engagement isn’t coming it’s here mobile guest engagement is now expected by your customers especiallyread more three technology trends for restaurants in  a lot happened in the restaurant industry in  anread more were here to help contact us news ncr receives worldatwork  seal of distinction recognized for outstanding commitment to employee engagement and total rewards effectiveness read more ncr corporation omnichannel journey design—is your business ready httpstcotkveso via crm blog what inspires our female leaders a qa for international womens day march th  marks international womens day an annual celebration of the social economic cultural and political achievements of women around the world as well as a chance to promote gender equality in the workplace and wider society read more did you know over  of the worlds  million atms are ncr machines attracting younger restaurant patrons with technology  ncr  world leader in consumer transaction technologies skip to main content ncr companycompanycompany overview interact global partners suppliers hospitality service partners technology partners locations executive leadership team corporate responsibility corporate governance investor relations locations solutionsfinancial services retail hospitality travel telecom  technology small business public sector product catalogall products productsncr atm solutions ncr pointofsale solutions airport airline  travel solutions cinemas  theaters solutions digital banking solutions banking branch transformation solutions department  specialty retail solutions food drug  mass merchandise solutions networking  collaboration solutions petroleum  convenience solutions postal automation solutions restaurant solutions telecom storefront solutions venues  stadium solutions wholesale distribution solutions servicesbanking services retail services restaurant services cinema  theater services venue  stadium services airline services airport services telecom  technology services government contact vehicles newsnewsroomnews releases ncr in the news ncr blogs resources media contacts bill nuti in the news awards and recognition careerscareers overview why work here blogs support contact us myncr language العربية arabic  chinese english uk english us english australia espa